        <h2>Real estate agent mortgage, structured right.</h2>
        <p>Top-producing residential real estate team leader, 8 years post-license at a major national brokerage, leading a 5-agent team. Personal Schedule C 1099 commission income of $385K in 2023 and $345K in 2024 (post-NAR-settlement adjustment year), 2-year average $365K. Team override revenue of $265K in 2023 and $225K in 2024 (averaging 35% of team agent GCI across 4 buyer&rsquo;s agents and 1 listing agent specialist), 2-year average $245K. Three rental investment properties generating $34K of Schedule E rental income annually with 4+ year history. eXp Realty Revenue Share income $19K annually from established downline sponsorship with 3-year history. Total $663K across personal commission + team override + rental + Revenue Share. S-corp election made 4 years ago: W-2 reasonable compensation $145K paid to the agent plus K-1 distributions from the S-corp covering the personal commission and team override revenue. Plus 18 active rental units in a separate LLC owned alongside the S-corp sales practice. The first lender saw the complex multi-entity structure with five distinct income streams, called the team override "variable and not stable for qualifying" even with 2-year documented history through the brokerage&rsquo;s team revenue-sharing agreement, refused the eXp Revenue Share entirely as "passive income not continuing employment," didn&rsquo;t run Form 1084 addbacks on the S-corp 1120-S to recover non-cash deductions for vehicle depreciation and home office, and offered the agent $625K Conventional based on the S-corp W-2 reasonable comp alone. We pulled the S-corp 1120-S returns for 2023 and 2024 with all K-1s, the personal 1040 with Schedule E for the rentals, the brokerage&rsquo;s team revenue-sharing agreement documenting the 35% override structure, the eXp Realty Revenue Share statements showing 3-year continuity from the downline sponsorship, the state real estate broker license, and the team brokerage affiliation documentation. Ran the S-corp W-2 + K-1 under <a href="https://selling-guide.fanniemae.com/sel/b3-3.4-02/analyzing-returns-partnership-or-s-corporation" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" style="color: var(--blue);">Fannie Mae B3-3.4-02</a> with full Form 1084 cash-flow addbacks at the S-corp level recovering vehicle depreciation, home office, and equipment depreciation, aggregated rental income under <a href="https://selling-guide.fanniemae.com/sel/b3-3.1-08/rental-income" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" style="color: var(--blue);">B3-3.1-08</a> with Schedule E Form 1084 addbacks for rental property depreciation, and the eXp Realty Revenue Share as continuing Schedule C self-employment under <a href="https://selling-guide.fanniemae.com/sel/b3-3.3-02/income-analysis-self-employed-borrowers" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" style="color: var(--blue);">B3-3.3-02</a>. Total qualifying income after Form 1084 normalization: $545K. Approved at $1.45M Conventional Jumbo for a Weston home with established home office and team operations space. Closed in 47 days. Multi-source top-producer realtor income with team override is the standard top-producer pattern &mdash; the first lender just didn&rsquo;t know how to read team revenue structure and S-corp Form 1084 addbacks properly.</p>
